        <h2>Postpartum Doula Care</h2>
        <p>
          The weeks after birth — often called the "fourth trimester" — can be both magical
          and overwhelming. Postpartum doula support gives your family the practical help
          and emotional grounding you need to settle in with confidence.
        </p>
        <p>
          I offer flexible day and evening packages to meet your family's schedule and needs.
        </p>
        <strong>What's included:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>Newborn care guidance and hands-on support</li>
          <li>Infant feeding support (breastfeeding, chestfeeding, or bottle feeding)</li>
          <li>Emotional check-ins and postpartum mood awareness</li>
          <li>Light household tasks (meal prep, dishes, laundry) so you can rest</li>
          <li>Sibling integration support</li>
          <li>Evidence-based information on newborn behavior and development</li>
          <li>Community resource referrals (lactation consultants, therapists, pediatricians)</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1.5rem; display:inline-block;">Inquire About Postpartum Support</a>
